      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have a REC switch on Yh92x. It turns out that in both cases - previous and this version, changing the switch position causes a keys blockage until it will be set back. So in this case it ends up on blocking recording screen and the user have to set back the switch. But i really don\u0027t know what to do with this, so i just want to say that we should avoid the REC button whenever it\u0027s possible in future, because its functionality doesn\u0027t fit to convention of buttons in rockbox. Something like this: { ACTION_STD_REC, BUTTON_REC|BUTTON_REL, BUTTON_REC|BUTTON_REPEAT }, could block the main screen, instead of the recording (recording will appear after setting it back), but i don\u0027t know what\u0027s better.",
